 } } \right]$$ satisfies the equation<br><br> $${A^{20}} + \alpha {A^{19}} + \beta A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 4 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$ for some real numbers $$\alpha$$ and $$\beta$$, then $$\beta$$ $$-$$ $$\alpha$$ is equal to ___________.

